<subSubSection id="C31C6500194EFF896A8BA74C7323F87D" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB9368B194EFF896A8BA74C71E5F8D1" blockId="110.[189,457,1835,1861]" box="[189,457,1835,1861]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">
<heading id="D0F181E7194EFF896A8BA74C71E5F8D1" bold="true" box="[189,457,1835,1861]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B972EA99194EFF896A8BA74C71E5F8D1" bold="true" box="[189,457,1835,1861]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B194EFF896A8BA73B7323F87D" blockId="110.[189,1399,1884,2025]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">
Very different from all other 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D08194EFF896822A73B72ADF8E2" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1822" box="[532,641,1884,1910]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B972EA99194EFF896822A73B72ADF8E2" box="[532,641,1884,1910]" italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Sphegina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and easily distinguished by the characters given in the key. The spoon-shaped lobe posteriorly on male sternum IV (without expanded apical part in other species) and the deeply bilobed surstylus, with the ventral lobe on the right side as long as the dorsal one (much shorter) are easily observed and unique characters.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31C6500194FFF886A8BA16E7113FEE1" pageId="111" pageNumber="112" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB9368B194FFF886A8BA16E7168FEB7" blockId="111.[189,324,265,291]" box="[189,324,265,291]" pageId="111" pageNumber="112">
<heading id="D0F181E7194FFF886A8BA16E7168FEB7" bold="true" box="[189,324,265,291]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="111" pageNumber="112" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B972EA99194FFF886A8BA16E7168FEB7" bold="true" box="[189,324,265,291]" pageId="111" pageNumber="112">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B194FFF886A8BA15F7113FEE1" blockId="111.[189,1399,312,373]" pageId="111" pageNumber="112">
The specific epithet is derived from the 
<typeStatus id="54BD8829194FFF8868ACA15F72E1FEC6" box="[666,717,312,338]" pageId="111" pageNumber="112">type</typeStatus>
locality, 
<collectingRegion id="49C2F869194FFF88690DA15F73D4FEC6" box="[827,1016,312,338]" country="India" name="Karnataka" pageId="111" pageNumber="112">Karnataka State</collectingRegion>
in 
<collectingCountry id="F311761B194FFF886E16A15F744CFEC6" box="[1056,1120,312,338]" name="India" pageId="111" pageNumber="112">India</collectingCountry>
. The name is a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
